title: SpaceX launches new cargo Dragon spacecraft to space station
summary: A brand new SpaceX Falcon 9 successfully launched a new cargo Dragon spacecraft Nov. 26, carrying supplies, experiments and new solar arrays for the International Space Station.

title: Moon Microscope, Solar Arrays Launch on NASA’s SpaceX Cargo Ship
summary: SpaceX’s 26th commercial resupply mission for NASA is on its way to the International Space Station.

title: Join us for a fireside chat with Lori Garver & Jim Bridenstine
summary: Together for the first time. She's a longtime SLS critic who served a decade in senior NASA roles under Clinton and Obama. He's a Republican ex-congressman who ran NASA for three years under Trump.

title: India’s PSLV rocket launches nine satellites in final mission of 2022
summary: India’s space agency ISRO launched a one-ton Earth observation satellite and eight nanosatellites to sun-synchronous polar orbit Nov. 26 aboard the nation’s workhorse Polar Satellite Launch Vehicle (PSLV) rocket.

title: NASA, SpaceX ready for second attempt to launch CRS-26 mission to ISS
summary: SpaceX’s newest Cargo Dragon 2 spacecraft, C211, will now launch atop a Falcon 9 rocket no earlier than 2:20 PM EST (19:20 UTC) on Saturday, Nov. 26 from Launch Complex 39A at NASA’s Kennedy Space Center (KSC). Following an on-time liftoff, Cargo Dragon will rendezvous and dock with the forward port on the Harmony module of the International Space Station (ISS) at 7:30 AM EST (12:30 UTC) on Sunday, Nov. 27.
